        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>
                <date>August 29 1835</date>
            </p>
            <p>My Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><sic>by</sic> your last letter you seem to think that I wish
                you<lb/> to engage with your congregation on their own Terms, no my good boy if
                you<lb/> are to be treated ill by them with out cause, I shall be the last man<lb/>
                to advise you to engage with them to be their slave, by no means<lb/> is that my
                wish, if you can have my other chance to get a <sic>Living</sic><lb/> and you
                certainly know if such chance you have, why then<lb/> let them get any body
                    <sic>Else</sic>, but I hope the case is not so bad<lb/> as you mention that you
                have no friends among them, I always<lb/> thought that at <sic>Least</sic> the most
                of the <add>יהודים</add> that is <persName>Mr Peixotto</persName><lb/>
                <persName>Ellen, Levy</persName>, <persName>Phillip. Levy</persName>
                <add>?</add>
                <persName><sic>goldsmith</sic></persName>, <persName>Philipe</persName>
                <persName>Cohens</persName>, <persName>Davis</persName><lb/> &amp;
                    <persName>Benjamin</persName> and some others I thought were your friends
                and<lb/> why they should all turn <sic>agains</sic> you I do not know how to
                account<lb/> for it I <sic>realy</sic> feel <sic>wery</sic> unpleasant on your acct,
                as for your<lb/>
                <sic>bording</sic> House, I should <sic>supose</sic> you might find some one
                who<lb/> would be glad to have you on reasonable terms may be also<lb/> for a
                    <sic>Lodger</sic> how ever you know best what suits you and<lb/> you will act
                    <sic>ackordingly</sic>; when I said I did not <sic>Liek</sic> the 2d<lb/> Trip
                with <add>?</add> I did not think you or she had any <add>?</add><lb/> motive but
                you ought to know that people will notice any<lb/> thing which would look
                    <sic>liek</sic> too much kindness, or attention<lb/> from any <add>?</add> to
                the <add>?</add> or from you to her was not right<lb/> I remember <persName>I
                    Seixas</persName> paid much attention to <persName><add>?</add>
                marks</persName>, and<lb/> the whole congregation of <placeName>Richmond</placeName>
                made a <add>?</add> talk of it<lb/> to his <add>?</add> so you can not blame any
                body to make the<lb/> remark of you, more I <add>?</add> say if you have any
                better<lb/> chance than you have at present give up your place if not<lb/> why you
                can <sic>Try</sic> for one year more <placeName><sic>Charlestown</sic></placeName>
                would sure<lb/> be more profit but the place is occationly<add>?</add> sickly,
                the<lb/> same years it is very <sic>Healthy</sic>! You say if you should get
                    <sic>marrit</sic><lb/> have you any body in your mind which will <sic>sute</sic>
                you let me know<lb/>
                <persName>Isaac</persName> I wish I was able to do for you something to your
                advantage<lb/> then I would say let them go to the—and come to me your welfare<lb/>
                is Dear to me, let me know when the <sic>comitty</sic> have met, what<lb/> was the
                result of it. I am your friend &amp; uncle <persName role="author">Zalma
                    Rehine</persName></p>
            <p> your Aunt sister <persName>saly<add>?</add></persName>
                <persName>Abby</persName>
                <persName>Reinah</persName> send <sic>there</sic> Love to you and<lb/> all
                    <persName>Mr. Peixottos</persName>
                <sic>famila</sic>, pray tell our friend <persName>Simah</persName> I should
                    <sic>liek</sic> to<lb/> get <sic>at</sic> line from her</p>
        </body>
